Kharadi (Marathi खऱाडी), is a suburb located on the banks of Mula-Mutha river off MH SH 27 (Pune-Ahmednagar State Highway) to the east of Pune city in India. A bypass road connecting Pune-Ahmednagar state highway to Pune-Solapur National highway passes through Kharadi. It is well connected to other parts of Pune city by PMPML buses.
